In <2u9cvn$adn@sunforest.mantis.co.uk> mathew@mantis.co.uk (mathew) writes:

>In article <dcosenzaCrs5pI.2yM@netcom.com>,  <dcosenza@netcom.com> wrote:
>>A couple of notes: keys that are larger than 1264 bits will not be readable
>>by previous versions of the software, so users who are interested in larger
>>key lengths are encouraged to move up.

>They'll also likely not be readable by *future* versions of PGP, so
>users interested in talking to the rest of the world are encouraged
>not to download this version.

>I wasn't consulted; indeed, I specifically asked that people *not*
>hack 2.6ui to use larger key sizes, as I wanted to make sure that any
>such change would be compatible with forthcoming official versions of PGP.

Why not?  2.6 is incompatible with all previous non-US versions, and some
previous legal US versions.  Why shouldn't 2.6ui be incompatible with 2.6?
